        "title": "Translation from Text to Touch -- Touching a “Japanese Old Tale”",
        "abstract": "The character display and interface through visual and auditory senses have been the focus of the Computer Human Interaction and also tactile sense interface has been studied. We propose a method for integrating character information and tactile sense, by focusing on the structure of texts and phonetic aspects of language. By using this method, we extract the tactile elements of “The Tale of the Heike, which has been handed down in Japan over a thousand years. Also, we extract the tactile elements of the English version of the tale and a passage from Hamlet and compare their tactile characteristics. ",
